full_text: @josephjefe Where in the #nflverse does snap data live?

Weekly snap counts including the division game, and our second bye of the season!! Starting with tight ends, as always, because there's not much to talk about with them. It's Kelce, and Gray gets a nice 50% of the snaps too. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/Mxo26IYEEf

Wide receivers!! Moore's snaps are right in line with where he was pre-injury, after dropping from a midseason high. Our favorite #2 WR still garnering #2 WR snaps, so that's something. Toney is INCREDIBLY efficient while getting Skyy Moore level snaps. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/UGVclbbr5x

Running Backs! McKinnon got more run this week, probably because they valued his consistency at pass blocking after Mahomes was injured. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/amrqIOJHWK
